content: Zeel Desai's personal information includes her name, email desaiazeel2128@vt.edu, LinkedIn profile (LinkedIN), Github profile (Github), LeetCode profile (Leetcode), GeeksforGeeks profile (GFG), phone number (+1)8046833534, and location USA.
She is pursuing a Master's of Science in Computer Science at Virginia Tech from July 2023 to May 2025, currently in her 1st semester.
Her coursework at Virginia Tech includes Machine Learning and Information Storage Retrieval
She completed her Bachelor's of Technology in Computer Science from Vellore Institute of Technology, Chennai, with a CGPA of 8.59 from August 2019 to May 2023.
Her undergraduate coursework included Data Structures & Algorithms, Software Engineering, Operating Systems, Object-Oriented Programming, Database Management Systems, and Networks.
Her programming skills include frameworks/tools like Python (ML & Statistical libraries), JavaScript, C++, SQL, R, PHP, and HTML/CSS.
She is experienced with technologies like Amazon Web Services, Scikit-learn, Pandas, NodeJS, React, TensorFlow, Git, and REST APIs.

As a Graduate Teaching Assistant for Machine Learning from August 2023 to May 2024, she conducted lectures on regression, supervised and unsupervised learning techniques, statistical & exploratory data analysis, and various basic machine learning & deep learning models.

As a Software Engineer Intern at Rarenature (Startup) from May 2021 to December 2021 in Singapore, she optimized database queries, designed efficient database schemes, and integrated third-party APIs to enhance application functionality, resulting in a 30% improvement in application development performance.

At Rarenature, she collaborated with the UI/UX team to implement responsive frontend design and prototyping, utilized agile tool JIRA and user-friendly interfaces for products, implemented version control using Git, facilitating written code review and documentation, testing, resulting in the identification of 15 defects.

As a Data Science Research Intern at Nagasaki University of Japan from June 2022 to October 2022, she incorporated contrastive learning into a knowledge distillation framework by collecting different web medical imaging modalities including X-ray, CT, and MRI, and achieved a scalable 94% accuracy

At Nagasaki University, she collaborated with cross-functional teams, prototyping usability models with healthcare professionals, to increase efficiency and scalability of the model by providing 1.8 million answers to 1,100,000 questions.

For the project Multi-class Transfer Learning in medical images using Explainable AI," she developed a model to detect CVDs from 4-class ECG images by Knowledge Distillation & applied ExAI techniques like LIME to generate heatmaps and highlight regions contributing most to the model's predictions."

For the project Instant Chat with Doctors," she fabricated a collaborative web application to provide healthcare facilities by developing a cross-functional portal for online consultation with doctors, appointment scheduling, secure file sharing, and front-end & back-end functionalities."
She has a publication titled Consumer Price Index forecasting using ARIMA and Holt's Winter Time Series models" (Link - Sept'22)."
She has a publication titled Deep transfer learning software for CVD prediction based on multi-class ECG images" (Link - Sept'22)."
She won the Quickest hands-on Prototype Builder" at Bajaj FinServ HackRx 2.0 among 2500+ participants in July 2021."
She qualified for Public Sapients JUMP START by clearing the aptitude & coding round in 35,000+ participants in June 2021.
She qualified for NTSE (National Talent Search Exam) Stage 1, securing an All India Rank in the top 100 from 80k participants in May 2017.
As a University Teacher Assistant, she assisted in tutorials, clarified concepts, and facilitated discussions for 100 students.
As a Student Co-ordinator, she executed events, handled finance & operations, and coordinated with over 500+ audience members.
